    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Flywheel and Flywheel Housing -
        Installation - Flexplate (Automatic Transmissions)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Flexplate (Automatic Transmissions)</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Allison 2000 Series Transmissions</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, if the vehicle is being re-configured with an Allison 2000 Series
                        transmission, make sure the correct flywheel housing is installed on the engine. Otherwise,
                        there will be interference between the flexplate studs and the flywheel housing that will only
                        be evident after the transmission has been installed.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two guide pins (made locally) in flexplate mounting bolt holes, 180&#176; from
                    each other.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3350014445" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figk10/K10005.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Adaptor hub, flexplate, and reinforcement ring</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M12 x 43 flexplate bolt (12)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Reinforcement ring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Paint marking index</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">AT adapter hub</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Flexplate assembly</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install AT adapter hub on guide pins.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When installed correctly, the ring gear of the flexplate is offset (not centered) toward the
                        transmission.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install flexplate assembly on the guide pins.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, make sure the reinforcement ring is installed with the paint mark or
                        XMSN SIDE facing outward (towards the transmission), otherwise, premature flexplate failure may
                        occur.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install reinforcement ring on the guide pins with paint mark (or XMSN SIDE) facing
                    outward.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install ten M12 x 43 flexplate bolts finger tight.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove guide pins and install remaining two M12 x 43 flexplate bolts finger tight.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten twelve M12 x 43 flexplate bolts to
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_365.xml" xrefid="t335001402">special torque</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335001402"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>MD-3000 Series World Transmissions</title>
            <figure id="f3350014446" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figK10/K10006.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Flexplate assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M12 x 45 flexplate bolt hole (12)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Reinforcement ring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft hub adapter</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M6 flexplate assembly bolt (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Flexplate assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Guide pin (2)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two guide pins (made locally) in flexplate mounting bolt holes, 180&#176; from
                    each other.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, make sure the paint mark, part number, or XMSN SIDE on the flexplate
                        is facing outward (towards the transmission).
                    </para>
                </caution>
                <note>
                    <para>The flexplate assembly is available as a complete assembled service part.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install flexplate assembly over the guide pins.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The following step applies to MD transmissions only.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install reinforcement ring with part number or logo facing out (towards the
                    transmission).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install ten M12 x 45 flexplate bolts finger tight.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove guide pins and install remaining two M12 x 45 flexplate bolts finger tight.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten M12 x 45 flexplate bolts to
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_365.xml" xrefid="t335001402">special torque</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335001402"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Flywheel and ring gear are part of the torque converter assembly.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
